item.description: The biggest con trick Israel has managed to pull off over the past two years is imposing entirely phoney parameters on a “debate” in the West about the credibility of the death toll in Gaza, now officially standing at just over 70,000. It is not just that we have been endlessly bogged down in rows about whether Gaza’s medical authorities can be trusted, or how many of the dead are Hamas fighters. (Despite Israeli disinformation campaigns, the Israeli military itself believes more than 80 per cent of the dead are civilians.) Or even that these “debates” always ignore the fact that, early on, Israel wrecked Gaza’s capacity to count its dead by destroying the enclave’s governmental offices and its hospitals. The 70,000 figure is likely to be a drastic under-estimate. No, the biggest con trick is that Israel has successfully penned us all into a “debate”, one entirely divorced from reality, that relates only to those killed directly by its bombs and gunfire. The truth is that far, far larger numbers of people in Gaza have been actively killed by Israel not through these direct means but through what statisticians refer to as “indirect” methods. These people were killed by Israel destroying their homes and leaving them with no shelter. By Israel destroying their water and electricity supplies and their sanitation systems. By Israel levelling their hospitals. By Israel starving them. By Israel creating the perfect conditions for disease to spread. The list of ways Israel is killing people in Gaza goes on and on. Imagine your own societies levelled in the way Gaza has been. How long would your elderly parents survive in this hellscape? How well would your diabetic child fare, or your sister with asthma, or your brother with cancer? How well would you cope with catching pneumonia, or even a common cold, if you hadn’t had more than one small meal a day for months on end? How would your wife deal with a difficult childbirth if there were no anaesthetics, or no hospital nearby, or a barely functioning hospital overwhelmed with victims from Israel’s latest bombing run. And what would be the chances of your baby surviving if its mother could produce no milk from her starvation diet? And if you could not give the baby formula feed because Israel was blocking supplies from entry into the enclave? And if, anyway, the contaminated water supply could not be mixed into the formula powder? None of these kinds of deaths are included in the figure of 70,000. And all precedents show that many, many times more people are killed through these indirect methods than directly through fatal injuries from bombs and bullets. According to a letter from experts in this field to the Lancet, studies of other wars – most of them far less destructive than Israel’s on the tiny enclave – indicate that between three and 15 times more people are killed by indirect, rather than direct, methods of warfare. The authors conservatively estimate an indirect death toll four times greater than the direct death toll. That would mean, at a minimum, 350,000 Palestinians have been killed in Gaza through Israel’s actions. The reality is likely to be even worse. That is without even mentioning the hundreds of thousands of Palestinians who have been left with horrific injuries and psychological trauma. Israel’s war planners know exactly how this direct-to-indirect ratio works. Which is why they chose to destroy nearly every home in Gaza, to bomb the power, sanitation and water facilities, to level the hospitals, and to block aid month after month. They knew this would be the way Israel could carry out a genocide while offering its allies – western governments and its army of lobbyists – a “get out of jail card” for their active complicity. Donald Trump’s so-called “ceasefire” is just another layer of deception in this endless game of smoke and mirrors. The UN’s child protection agency, Unicef, reports that less than a quarter of aid trucks are getting into Gaza, past Israel’s continuing starvation blockade, despite Israeli commitments agreed as part of the “ceasefire”. Apparently, this doesn’t register as a gross ceasefire violation. It goes unnoticed. Unicef reports further that in October alone, at the start of the “ceasefire”, nearly 18,000 new mothers and babies had to be hospitalised in Gaza from acute malnutrition. The genocide isn’t over. Israel may have slowed the rate of direct killings it is committing by bombing Gaza, but the indirect killings continue unabated. And so does the Israeli-engineered “debate” in the West, one designed to obscure and excuse the mass murder of Gaza’s population. item.title: Roblox is a disgusting company run by pedophiles and more people need to be aware
item.description:
My reaction to every stage of this fucked up nightmare saga. Not enough people know what's going on. If you are a parent or know children who play Roblox, please, I am begging you, get them on a different game. Here we go: Many years ago, a Roblox user named Schlep ( https://www.youtube.com/@RealSchlep ), underage at the time, was abused by a popular player. In response, he made it his life's work to catch pedophiles on his favourite game. He did it entirely within the bounds of the law, even teaming up with his local police department. He successfully took down FOUR predators who were using Roblox to lure children. Arguably a good thing to do. The only people who could possibly be upset by this are pedophiles, yes?
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hMqAw_NjHK8 Roblox banned him. Not only did they ban him, they targeted anything remotely related to him and removed it from their platform entirely. They said he was a dangerous vigilante, who broke the platform's Terms of Service. In response, Schlep dropped this video, disputing all the allegations. It drew plenty of attention, including that of Chris Hansen. I'm sure I don't need to tell you who that is. His fans kept making "Free Schlep" content in Roblox, which was all removed. The CEO responded personally by accusing Schlep of being "just as bad as the predators," and began months worth of smear campaigning, while Schlep turned to lawyers.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vIcVPPOB8TQ Seriously, if you're on the wrong side of Chris Hansen, you really need to start asking some major questions.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6dksQJulz4c Last month, things spiked. In spite of Schlep's insistence that no one at Roblox contact him except through his lawyer, the CEO himself reached out, privately. He offered to reinstate Schlep's account...if he would just...shut up. At the same time as he was begging Schlep to be quiet about the predators on his platform, the CEO was on stage, telling the same lies about him. Insisting he was a dangerous person, who they kicked off the platform for safety. And then, he turns around and announces that he wants to start a DATING PLATFORM ON ROBLOX. Yes, you read that right, the CEO of a children's game accused of harbouring predators wants to include DATING. He's on camera saying that the predators are an "opportunity". Some people say he meant they're an opportunity to 'increase security', but let's examine that. In the video above, Schlep is on stage with Chris Hansen and an actual police officer, discussing the state of Roblox. This officer mentions that he reached out to Roblox, personally, offering very basic things they could change to increase safety for children on the platform. To which they did...nothing. And as of a few weeks ago, the CEO of Roblox went on record saying he was considering adding, and I quote, "Child Gambling". Roblox was a good platform for children. And it is still one of the most popular ones. Why am I making this post? In the hopes that parents will see it, will look at the videos, and will find out what a threat this game is to their children. Especially now that they've ramped up their advertising to every platform they can. During the holidays, when you see your extended family, make sure you're protecting your children, your siblings, your cousins, your niblings, and yourselves. Happy Holidays to all, and to all...what the fuck is happening to the world.

item.title: I did it! I kicked their scummy, evil asses!
item.description: This is a long story but tldr of the previous posts. Went to fight for the Ukrainians, left a paid rented apartment and told the landlords it's secured and I will be back in a couple months and resume living there. They scammed me, rented it out to someone else and pocketed what I paid. Afterwards they got convicted of fraud and I sued them.  --------- It's been a long fight but the court ruled in my favour today! I won! Their new lawyer screwed the pooch so hard today it's impossible not to laugh. He introduced a new piece of BS that was supposed to delay the whole thing again but it completely and utterly contradicted most of the previous ones... We caught it after it got submitted and nailed them in front of the judge who decided he's sick of it. Tore them a new one and ruled in my favour. I got rent and security deposit for the rest of the unrealized lease (14 months) plus court and lawyer costs. Plus rent on the place I had after that, lost wages and property. Their assets are frozen so they're gonna pay up if they want it or not.  Lawyer advises me that it's gonna take 6 months to a year cause courts are slow and overloaded so it's not over just now but it's a matter of time. It cost me 75k PLN (30 of which I still owe and can't delay paying off). I'm homeless and couch surfing until Christmas, then I got no idea what. My mental health is gone, my PTSD is so bad it's a wonder i didn't hurt anyone yet. I'm barely eating, maybe 800 calories a day to afford dog food. I'm a wreck... But I won and they got what's coming to them.  Still can't find stable employment, doing emergency plumbing and Uber  If anybody can help me last through this I would be forever grateful. I got a couple avenues for it.  I'm gonna go driving now, just wanted to share the good news Also if you live in the tricity area of Poland and have a cheap place to stay you're willing to rent for a while or work to offer, dm me please revolut: @jacek5f0e wise: @jacekn52 paypal: DM me Ko-fi: ko-fi.com/tyrcarter
